<p>Weekly writing about how technology and people intersect. By day, I&#8217;m building <a href="https://www.daybreakventures.com/">Daybreak</a> to partner with early-stage founders. By night, I&#8217;m writing <a href="https://www.digitalnative.tech/">Digital Native</a> about market trends and startup opportunities.</p><p>If you haven&#8217;t subscribed, join 55,000+ weekly readers by subscribing here:</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.digitalnative.tech/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.digitalnative.tech/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><div><hr></div><h1>Business-in-a-Box 2.0</h1><p>When we think of franchises, we tend to think of McDonald&#8217;s and Subway. </p><p>McDonald&#8217;s operates about 40,000 global restaurants; around 37,000 of those (92.5%) are franchised. Subway trails McDonald&#8217;s as the world&#8217;s 2nd-largest franchise (though it actually has more US locations), and is 100% franchised. Familiar names <a href="https://americasbestfranchises.com/blog/the-biggest-franchises-in-the-world-in-2023/">round out</a> the top five: KFC (#3), 7-Eleven (#4), Burger King (#5). </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg" width="1456" height="764" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:764,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;McDonald's Franchise | Cost, Fees &amp; Earning Stats (2024)&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="McDonald's Franchise | Cost, Fees &amp; Earning Stats (2024)" title="McDonald's Franchise | Cost, Fees &amp; Earning Stats (2024)" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2848722c-40b1-40b7-9be0-229e2f2efde2_1800x945.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">McDonald&#8217;s is the world&#8217;s largest franchiser; franchisees pay McDonald&#8217;s a $45 franchise fee</figcaption></figure></div><p>But franchises go well beyond fast food. </p><p>The first franchise is thought to date back to 1888, when an enterprising woman named Martha Matilda Harper came up with a new way to shampoo. And Harper certainly had the hair to back up her innovation: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg" width="446" height="677.6243093922652" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:550,&quot;width&quot;:362,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:446,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Women of History: Martha Matilda Harper - Mary Baker Eddy Library&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Women of History: Martha Matilda Harper - Mary Baker Eddy Library" title="Women of History: Martha Matilda Harper - Mary Baker Eddy Library" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82014a26-690a-42fd-a6a4-f03563589998_362x550.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Martha Matilda Harper, the first franchisor</figcaption></figure></div><p>Damn. </p><p>Harper began to franchise her shampooing methods to other women, eventually offering those women everything from training, to branded products, to advertising, to group insurance. In return, Harper would take a share of their proceeds. At its peak, Harper Salons grew to 500 salons and training schools, lifting hundreds of low-income women from poverty and minting a new breed of entrepreneur. </p><p>Fast-forward to modern-day, and haircare remains popular for franchising. Until I got fed up with having a bowl cut, I was a loyal patron of Great Clips. There are 4,400 franchised Great Clips salons in the US and Canada, making Great Clips the world&#8217;s largest salon brand. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg" width="1172" height="847" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/f2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:847,&quot;width&quot;:1172,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:291422,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff2053710-daa4-45d7-a443-30fb843052f7_1172x847.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">If you&#8217;ve ever gotten a bowl cut from Great Clips, you too have participated in the franchise economy (Photo: Rex circa 1997)</figcaption></figure></div><p>The International Franchise Association estimates that there are about 792,000 franchise establishments in the US, employing 8.5M people and raking in $825B in annual revenue. </p><p>Shoutout to my friend Molly Alter for putting Harper salons on my radar; Molly <a href="https://northzone.com/2023/12/15/perspectives-freeing-smbs-from-franchises-through-ai/">wrote an excellent recent piece</a> on franchises. She and I have been discussing the concept in depth because we&#8217;re seeing the same trend in the Pre-Seed and Seed markets: the return of &#8220;business-in-a-box.&#8221; </p><p>Business-in-a-box was a startup term in vogue a few years back, referring to startups that allow people to&#8230;well, to launch businesses. There have been a few major success stories in business-in-a-box (more on those below) and we&#8217;re now seeing a <em>new</em> generation of business-in-the-box companies emerge, powered by both technological and cultural shifts. This is one of the foremost trends I&#8217;ve been seeing this year in early-stage venture. </p><p>On the <em>technology</em> front, generative AI automates workflows, removing the complexities of launching and managing a business. We saw the same thing with software, which digitized cumbersome pen-and-paper tasks. But AI is an order-of-magnitude more efficient at abstracting away the headaches and grunt work of entrepreneurship. </p><p>On the <em>cultural</em> front, we&#8217;re seeing a shift to more flexible, self-driven work. This is a recurring theme in Digital Native. Gen Z in particular wants to forgo traditional forms of work in favor of more autonomous options. Survey after survey confirms this. <a href="https://news.samsung.com/us/gen-z-defining-future-work-own-terms-reveals-morning-consult-samsung-survey/">A recent Samsung + Morning Consult report</a> found that 50% of Gen Zs aspire to start their own business. <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/survey-genz-may-be-the-most-entrepreneurial-of-all-generations-183626972.html?">Research from ZenBusiness</a> found that 84% of Gen Zs selected entrepreneurship as the most exciting of 12 possible career paths, with 75% saying they want to become entrepreneurs.</p><p>We also see a post-COVID effect. Self-employment is currently at its highest share of workers since before the Great Recession. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8cdc873e-73e8-4771-bea8-67cbba8086c3_1296x790.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8cdc873e-73e8-4771-bea8-67cbba8086c3_1296x790.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8cdc873e-73e8-4771-bea8-67cbba8086c3_1296x790.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8cdc873e-73e8-4771-bea8-67cbba8086c3_1296x790.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8cdc873e-73e8-4771-bea8-67cbba8086c3_1296x790.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8cdc873e-73e8-4771-bea8-67cbba8086c3_1296x790.png" width="1296" height="790" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/8cdc873e-73e8-4771-bea8-67cbba8086c3_1296x790.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:790,&quot;width&quot;:1296,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;More Americans Are Self-Employed Than Any Time Since 2008 Crisis - Bloomberg&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;More Americans Are Self-Employed Than Any Time Since 2